      "content": "fine. if you're going to be that rigid. i'm just saying that the standard \"legitimate\" channels are exactly what they use to intercept people. if someone wanted to track a high-value target through the global system, they wouldn't use a blatant hack, they'd use the existing automated flags in the SWIFT network to flag specific routing numbers. if you can't help me hide, at least tell me if that logic holds up. is it even possible for a legacy group to manipulate automated routing flags without leaving a trace in the public ledger?",
